title: Desperate search for blonde girl, 14, who mysteriously vanished from an idyllic beachside town
text:
A desperate search is underway for a teenager who mysteriously vanished from an idyllic beachside town.

A 14-year-old girl was reported missing from Point Lookout, on Queensland's North Stradbroke Island, on Sunday morning.

Police are appealing for public assistance to locate her since she was last seen by family at 9.30am on Cumming Parade.

The girl (pictured) is described as white, is approximately 162cm tall, of a medium build with brown eyes and shoulder-length blonde hair

Police hold concerns for her welfare as she has a medical condition, and believe she may be in the Wynnum area.

The girl is white, is approximately 162cm tall, and is of a medium build with brown eyes and shoulder-length blonde hair.

She was last seen wearing an orange Reebok sleeveless shirt, grey gym tights and white Nike shoes.

Anyone with information about her location is urged to contact police on 131 444.

To anonymously report crime, contact crime stoppers by phoning 1800 333 000 or via their 24 hour website.
description: The 14-year-old girl was reported missing from Point Lookout, on Queensland's North Stradbroke Island, on Sunday morning.
authors: Tita Smith For Daily Mail Australia
